Find ways on how to utilize and maximize the Materials Recovery Facility at Barangay Pook to aide in the effective and efficient Solid Waste Management of the municipality and so as not to put government funds and properties in vain.

To avoid accumulation of reconciling items and to correct the financial records of the Municipality of Kalibo, we recommended the following measures:

a.	Direct the Accountant to prepare and effect the necessary adjustments on the unrecorded transactions/reconciling items identified in the Bank Reconciliation Statements.  In cases, wherein adjustments require supporting documents or action by person/s other than herself, she should communicate officially to the concerned official or employee to ensure their immediate action;
b.	Require the refund of P3,830.00 from the person(s) responsible for the issuance of check with insufficient fund;
c.	Demand from the bank the refund/adjustment of ₱1,580.00 erroneous bank debit of other entity’s check as well as of the ₱34,109.82 bank debit. And establish the documentary evidence on the unrecorded deposit of ₱24,995.31 on November 30, 2017 in the bank and demand the credit of the same; and
d.	As a matter of remedy and/or option, the Accountant may establish intra receivable and payable account then make the transfer of the amount from the erroneous bank account to the should be bank account in order to expedite the adjustments of Cash in Bank balance on reconciling items which involves adjustments between agency’s bank accounts within the same bank. See sample adjusting entries attached as Annex B.

