We recommended the following measures in order to ensure the validity of claims and immediate payment of the accounts payable:

Set a cut-off date for the submission of purchase requests from the different offices of the Municipality every December of each year to give ample time for the procurement and ensure actual delivery before the end of December;

Payables aging 2 years and more without valid creditors/complete supporting documents be reverted to prior year’s adjustments;

Refrain from issuing Purchase Orders at the last week of December of each year; and

All cash advances be fully liquidated at the end of the year.

We recommended the following measures in order to ensure the validity of claims and immediate payment of the accounts payable:
Set a cut-off date for the submission of purchase requests from the different offices of the Municipality every December of each year to give ample time for the procurement and ensure actual delivery before the end of December;

Identify all unpaid payables if these are valid, that is, if supported with proper documents. If not, revert these unliquidated payables to prior years’ adjustments to have funds available for supplemental appropriations; 

Refrain from issuing Purchase Orders at the last week of December of each year;

De-obligate the obligations pertaining to undelivered goods or unaccomplished services at cut-off date prior to closing of books at year-end; and

All cash advances shall be fully liquidated at the end of the year.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the officials/employees concern to:

Submit copies of document/standard form of the request for quotation communicated to and duly received by the three suppliers engaged in the negotiated purchase of the motor vehicle showing the identical item and descriptions;

Submit an affidavit as to the actual terms and conditions either it was for delivery or pick-up; 

Submit an affidavit that the payment of the motor vehicle was done after delivery or prior to delivery; 

It is recommended that the details of procurement or any agreements/stipulations be indicated in the Price Quotations and Purchase Orders (PO) for negotiated purchase to conform with existing procurement rules and regulations; and

Refrain from making advance payments on goods not delivered to avoid risks of possible losses due to fortuitous events, accidents and/or theft.

